  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The model is intended to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. A full 13-factor assessment was conducted: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Submitted under the Minimal profile; structured Context of Use metadata is captured in the binding claim and requirement nodes per the submitting organization's document-management convention.",
